00:05:49.896 --> 00:05:52.320 align:middle line:84%
>> You see none of this is a
true understanding of shame.

00:05:52.320 --> 00:05:55.620 align:middle line:90%


00:05:55.620 --> 00:05:57.775 align:middle line:84%
Most of us say shame is a
feeling of unworthiness.

00:05:57.775 --> 00:05:59.400 align:middle line:84%
That's a most common
answer that you'll

00:05:59.400 --> 00:06:02.170 align:middle line:84%
get because that's what's been
propagated over and over again.

00:06:02.170 --> 00:06:04.540 align:middle line:84%
It's a feeling of not
being good enough.

00:06:04.540 --> 00:06:06.780 align:middle line:84%
That's not actually
what shame is.

00:06:06.780 --> 00:06:10.260 align:middle line:84%
And the emotion that we
have that we call shame

00:06:10.260 --> 00:06:13.110 align:middle line:84%
is actually secondary
to what shame is,

00:06:13.110 --> 00:06:16.870 align:middle line:84%
which is a biological
affective reaction.

00:06:16.870 --> 00:06:19.320 align:middle line:84%
Now you guys do know
it biological affective

00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:22.770 align:middle line:84%
reactions are because you
know what fight or flight is.

00:06:22.770 --> 00:06:26.130 align:middle line:84%
Fight or flight is an example
of a biological affective

00:06:26.130 --> 00:06:27.450 align:middle line:90%
reaction.

00:06:27.450 --> 00:06:32.460 align:middle line:84%
You can't not flinch if
something comes up to your face

00:06:32.460 --> 00:06:35.357 align:middle line:90%
and does that to you, can you?

00:06:35.357 --> 00:06:36.940 align:middle line:84%
What if I told you
shame was the same?

00:06:36.940 --> 00:06:39.520 align:middle line:90%


00:06:39.520 --> 00:06:40.550 align:middle line:90%
So what does this mean?

00:06:40.550 --> 00:06:43.970 align:middle line:84%
If shame in and of itself is a
biological affective reaction,

00:06:43.970 --> 00:06:45.650 align:middle line:90%
you can't get away from it.

00:06:45.650 --> 00:06:48.290 align:middle line:90%
It's not going to happen.

00:06:48.290 --> 00:06:53.610 align:middle line:84%
Now what we're calling
shame is a self-concept.

00:06:53.610 --> 00:06:55.590 align:middle line:84%
Actually it's just
a cascade of effects

00:06:55.590 --> 00:06:58.230 align:middle line:84%
that happen in the
psyche as a result of how

00:06:58.230 --> 00:07:02.157 align:middle line:84%
we respond to that biological
affective reaction.

00:07:02.157 --> 00:07:03.990 align:middle line:84%
This will make more
sense when I demonstrate

00:07:03.990 --> 00:07:05.700 align:middle line:90%
this entire thing on stage.

00:07:05.700 --> 00:07:08.340 align:middle line:84%
But the preface
is we got to stop

00:07:08.340 --> 00:07:10.540 align:middle line:90%
