00:07:38.500 --> 00:07:42.580 align:middle line:84%
Now before we introduce you to
mom's role in this whole thing,

00:07:42.580 --> 00:07:44.680 align:middle line:90%
I need you to get something.

00:07:44.680 --> 00:07:47.590 align:middle line:84%
As a social species for
thousands upon thousands

00:07:47.590 --> 00:07:50.320 align:middle line:84%
of years, your survival
depended upon your closeness

00:07:50.320 --> 00:07:51.680 align:middle line:90%
with the social group.

00:07:51.680 --> 00:07:53.175 align:middle line:90%
And it's no different today.

00:07:53.175 --> 00:07:54.550 align:middle line:84%
I love it when
people say they're

00:07:54.550 --> 00:07:57.470 align:middle line:84%
independent because
it's complete BS.

00:07:57.470 --> 00:08:00.100 align:middle line:84%
You're completely dependent
on whether somebody makes sure

00:08:00.100 --> 00:08:02.195 align:middle line:84%
that there's a road for
you to drive on today.

00:08:02.195 --> 00:08:03.820 align:middle line:84%
What would happen
today-- swear to God,

00:08:03.820 --> 00:08:05.150 align:middle line:90%
just think about it right now--

00:08:05.150 --> 00:08:06.775 align:middle line:84%
there's no more food
the grocery store.

00:08:06.775 --> 00:08:08.020 align:middle line:90%
What do you do?

00:08:08.020 --> 00:08:11.050 align:middle line:84%
Most of you in a metropolitan
city die by the way.

00:08:11.050 --> 00:08:13.614 align:middle line:90%
So you're totally dependent.

00:08:13.614 --> 00:08:16.400 align:middle line:90%


00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:17.410 align:middle line:90%
And even beyond that.

00:08:17.410 --> 00:08:19.500 align:middle line:84%
We're dependent upon
others because we

00:08:19.500 --> 00:08:21.880 align:middle line:90%
have emotional needs.

00:08:21.880 --> 00:08:25.980 align:middle line:84%
And regardless of what you have
heard in the spiritual field,

00:08:25.980 --> 00:08:29.052 align:middle line:84%
those emotional needs
cannot be met by you.

00:08:29.052 --> 00:08:31.260 align:middle line:84%
I realize that I'm going to
get aggressive with this,

00:08:31.260 --> 00:08:32.409 align:middle line:90%
and most people don't like it.

00:08:32.409 --> 00:08:33.209 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:08:33.209 --> 00:08:35.820 align:middle line:84%
Because so many of us find our
way into the spiritual field

00:08:35.820 --> 00:08:40.350 align:middle line:84%
because we have
been hurt by people.

00:08:40.350 --> 00:08:42.640 align:middle line:84%
You don't go looking for God
if your family's awesome.

00:08:42.640 --> 00:08:45.480 align:middle line:90%
You don't.

00:08:45.480 --> 00:08:47.700 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:08:47.700 --> 00:08:49.650 align:middle line:84%
You go looking for
things like that

00:08:49.650 --> 00:08:52.380 align:middle line:84%
when you need to find love from
somewhere else, because you're

00:08:52.380 --> 00:08:53.580 align:middle line:90%
not getting it.

00:08:53.580 --> 00:08:55.800 align:middle line:84%
Now it's really
profoundly painful

00:08:55.800 --> 00:08:58.650 align:middle line:84%
to not get those
emotional needs met.

00:08:58.650 --> 00:09:02.250 align:middle line:84%
So what we do is we gravitate
towards spiritual philosophies

00:09:02.250 --> 00:09:05.850 align:middle line:84%
that tell us, you
don't need to need it.

00:09:05.850 --> 00:09:10.500 align:middle line:84%
Everything you want,
you can find within.

00:09:10.500 --> 00:09:14.670 align:middle line:84%
But in my view, this is not
only a complete rejection

00:09:14.670 --> 00:09:20.370 align:middle line:84%
of ourselves as people,
it's causing so much damage

00:09:20.370 --> 00:09:22.710 align:middle line:84%
on the planet today to
stay as disconnected

00:09:22.710 --> 00:09:24.450 align:middle line:90%
as we are from each other.

00:09:24.450 --> 00:09:26.340 align:middle line:84%
Why aren't we teaching
people to have

00:09:26.340 --> 00:09:31.140 align:middle line:84%
intimate relationships and
lifelong connections instead?

00:09:31.140 --> 00:09:32.960 align:middle line:90%
Are you with me?

00:09:32.960 --> 00:09:34.870 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:09:34.870 --> 00:09:35.670 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:09:35.670 --> 00:09:38.580 align:middle line:90%


00:09:38.580 --> 00:09:41.910 align:middle line:84%
Even back in the cave
days and still today, you

00:09:41.910 --> 00:09:45.960 align:middle line:84%
have to be close to the people
in your life experience.

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:47.760 align:middle line:90%
Closeness is everything.

00:09:47.760 --> 00:09:51.120 align:middle line:84%
If you took a tiny baby, even
today, just tiny little baby,

00:09:51.120 --> 00:09:55.560 align:middle line:84%
laid them out on the
sidewalk, it takes hours

00:09:55.560 --> 00:09:57.300 align:middle line:90%
before that child's dead.

00:09:57.300 --> 00:10:00.250 align:middle line:84%
You are totally
relationally dependent.

00:10:00.250 --> 00:10:02.520 align:middle line:84%
And this is extreme
for a physical human,

00:10:02.520 --> 00:10:06.790 align:middle line:84%
more so than it is for
another animal species.

00:10:06.790 --> 00:10:08.220 align:middle line:90%
So a deer, right?

00:10:08.220 --> 00:10:09.280 align:middle line:90%
Let's just take a deer.

00:10:09.280 --> 00:10:12.390 align:middle line:84%
A deer is born, and
within hours, it's up,

00:10:12.390 --> 00:10:14.400 align:middle line:90%
and it's roaming around.

00:10:14.400 --> 00:10:17.070 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have to nurse
on its mother for years,

00:10:17.070 --> 00:10:19.690 align:middle line:90%
you know what I mean?

00:10:19.690 --> 00:10:20.490 align:middle line:90%
That's a deer.

00:10:20.490 --> 00:10:22.030 align:middle line:90%
That's better than a human.

00:10:22.030 --> 00:10:22.980 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:10:22.980 --> 00:10:27.450 align:middle line:84%
We are not walking
around up to deer

00:10:27.450 --> 00:10:29.890 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of some
meadow and saying,

00:10:29.890 --> 00:10:34.770 align:middle line:84%
you know, you're pretty
dependent on your social group.

00:10:34.770 --> 00:10:37.650 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking you should probably
develop some independence

00:10:37.650 --> 00:10:41.140 align:middle line:84%
because they could
leave you one day.

00:10:41.140 --> 00:10:41.940 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:10:41.940 --> 00:10:44.313 align:middle line:84%
You wouldn't do that
to a deer, would you?

00:10:44.313 --> 00:10:45.480 align:middle line:90%
We wouldn't do it to a deer.

00:10:45.480 --> 00:10:46.560 align:middle line:90%
We don't do it to horses.

00:10:46.560 --> 00:10:48.930 align:middle line:84%
We understand why dogs
go to hell when they're

00:10:48.930 --> 00:10:52.410 align:middle line:90%
stuck in a pen by themselves.

00:10:52.410 --> 00:10:55.540 align:middle line:90%
But we expect this of ourselves.

00:10:55.540 --> 00:10:57.390 align:middle line:90%
I got a problem with this.

00:10:57.390 --> 00:10:59.550 align:middle line:84%
Because, yet again, so
much of spirituality

00:10:59.550 --> 00:11:01.500 align:middle line:84%
is about denying
our physicality,

00:11:01.500 --> 00:11:03.850 align:middle line:90%
denying our biology.

00:11:03.850 --> 00:11:06.450 align:middle line:84%
We need to integrate our biology
and integrate our humanity,

00:11:06.450 --> 00:11:08.952 align:middle line:90%
not try to get away from it.

00:11:08.952 --> 00:11:11.856 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:11:11.856 --> 00:11:16.220 align:middle line:90%


00:11:16.220 --> 00:11:19.570 align:middle line:84%
So let's look at how shame
fits into the picture.

00:11:19.570 --> 00:11:21.450 align:middle line:90%
This is mom.

00:11:21.450 --> 00:11:24.400 align:middle line:84%
Now mom wants the
best for us, right?

00:11:24.400 --> 00:11:26.380 align:middle line:84%
It's a rare parent that's
like, I deliberately

00:11:26.380 --> 00:11:29.050 align:middle line:90%
want to destroy your life.

00:11:29.050 --> 00:11:32.320 align:middle line:90%
Maybe some of you had those.

00:11:32.320 --> 00:11:35.350 align:middle line:84%
But what she's not going to
be aware that she's doing

00:11:35.350 --> 00:11:40.120 align:middle line:84%
is going into an
attitude of disapproval.

00:11:40.120 --> 00:11:42.730 align:middle line:84%
The socialization process is
about reward and punishment.

00:11:42.730 --> 00:11:44.980 align:middle line:84%
It's about approval
and disapproval.

00:11:44.980 --> 00:11:49.720 align:middle line:84%
And so a child doesn't have
to even receive words in order

00:11:49.720 --> 00:11:51.050 align:middle line:90%
to perceive that judgment.

00:11:51.050 --> 00:11:53.620 align:middle line:84%
I know you know what it's
like when your mom or dad just

00:11:53.620 --> 00:11:56.470 align:middle line:90%
casts you that look, right?

00:11:56.470 --> 00:11:59.210 align:middle line:90%


00:11:59.210 --> 00:12:02.050 align:middle line:90%
This is what happens.

00:12:02.050 --> 00:12:03.590 align:middle line:90%
I'm using you guys.

00:12:03.590 --> 00:12:05.580 align:middle line:90%
OK, so, mom, over there.

00:12:05.580 --> 00:12:06.830 align:middle line:90%
What do you disapprove of?

00:12:06.830 --> 00:12:10.950 align:middle line:84%
Put yourself in the
scenario in childhood.

00:12:10.950 --> 00:12:12.360 align:middle line:90%
She's five.

00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:13.536 align:middle line:90%
Let's make her five.

00:12:13.536 --> 00:12:15.240 align:middle line:90%
>> Bothering me.

00:12:15.240 --> 00:12:17.755 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:12:17.755 --> 00:12:20.620 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, so I [INAUDIBLE].

00:12:20.620 --> 00:12:22.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Why are you bothering her?

00:12:22.900 --> 00:12:25.780 align:middle line:90%


00:12:25.780 --> 00:12:27.916 align:middle line:84%
>> Because I want
to know things.

00:12:27.916 --> 00:12:30.790 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't have time.

00:12:30.790 --> 00:12:32.230 align:middle line:90%
I don't have time.

00:12:32.230 --> 00:12:34.250 align:middle line:84%
I have too much
going on in my head.

00:12:34.250 --> 00:12:36.778 align:middle line:90%
I need to focus on me.

00:12:36.778 --> 00:12:37.820 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, did you feel that?

00:12:37.820 --> 00:12:40.370 align:middle line:84%
So that was actually
a pretty light one.

00:12:40.370 --> 00:12:44.470 align:middle line:84%
But if you were to look at
the energy between them,

00:12:44.470 --> 00:12:46.630 align:middle line:84%
is what she just did
a push-away or a pull?

00:12:46.630 --> 00:12:48.797 align:middle line:90%
>> Push-away.

00:12:48.797 --> 00:12:51.130 align:middle line:84%
>> I want you to get really
attuned to this, by the way,

00:12:51.130 --> 00:12:54.640 align:middle line:84%
because there are two primary
movements within the universe

00:12:54.640 --> 00:12:56.590 align:middle line:90%
when it comes to relationships--

00:12:56.590 --> 00:13:00.790 align:middle line:84%
to push away and to
include as part of oneself.

00:13:00.790 --> 00:13:03.130 align:middle line:84%
So away and towards--
these are the two movements

00:13:03.130 --> 00:13:04.960 align:middle line:84%
you need to concern
yourself with so as

00:13:04.960 --> 00:13:07.720 align:middle line:90%
to understand this full picture.

00:13:07.720 --> 00:13:10.930 align:middle line:84%
When a parent does something,
say something, or even

00:13:10.930 --> 00:13:14.840 align:middle line:84%
just emits the energy of
pushing away their child,

00:13:14.840 --> 00:13:18.800 align:middle line:84%
what happens to the nervous
system of the child?

00:13:18.800 --> 00:13:20.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Fight or flight.

00:13:20.230 --> 00:13:21.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Fight or flight.

00:13:21.770 --> 00:13:27.410 align:middle line:84%
This child has to re-establish
closeness immediately.

00:13:27.410 --> 00:13:32.380 align:middle line:84%
What has she made an enemy of
in this particular circumstance?

00:13:32.380 --> 00:13:33.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Questions.

00:13:33.880 --> 00:13:35.880 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:13:35.880 --> 00:13:38.303 align:middle line:90%
>> Needs.

00:13:38.303 --> 00:13:40.470 align:middle line:84%
What it is that when a kid
wants to know the answer,

00:13:40.470 --> 00:13:42.250 align:middle line:84%
when they want your
time, it's like--

00:13:42.250 --> 00:13:43.050 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:13:43.050 --> 00:13:46.350 align:middle line:84%
And so what the child perceives
in this circumstance is

00:13:46.350 --> 00:13:50.610 align:middle line:84%
it's not OK to need me,
it's not OK to want me.

00:13:50.610 --> 00:13:54.480 align:middle line:84%
So the child, even on
a subconscious level,

00:13:54.480 --> 00:13:58.740 align:middle line:84%
what's getting rejected
in me is the need for mom.

00:13:58.740 --> 00:14:00.910 align:middle line:90%
That is not OK.

00:14:00.910 --> 00:14:03.030 align:middle line:84%
So what she has to
do to re-establish

00:14:03.030 --> 00:14:08.490 align:middle line:84%
a relationship with her mother
is to triangulate internally.

00:14:08.490 --> 00:14:11.850 align:middle line:84%
You guys understand
triangulation yet?

00:14:11.850 --> 00:14:13.420 align:middle line:90%
This is really cool.

00:14:13.420 --> 00:14:14.220 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:14:14.220 --> 00:14:14.910 align:middle line:90%
I know you do.

00:14:14.910 --> 00:14:16.035 align:middle line:90%
You just don't know you do.

00:14:16.035 --> 00:14:17.220 align:middle line:90%
Ready for this?

00:14:17.220 --> 00:14:19.637 align:middle line:84%
Pretend they're not who they
are in their roles right now.

00:14:19.637 --> 00:14:21.940 align:middle line:84%
Pretend that she and
I, we know each other,

00:14:21.940 --> 00:14:23.580 align:middle line:90%
and we also know her.

00:14:23.580 --> 00:14:26.738 align:middle line:84%
Triangulation is, you
know, I don't really

00:14:26.738 --> 00:14:28.530 align:middle line:84%
think she should have
treated you that way.

00:14:28.530 --> 00:14:31.590 align:middle line:90%


00:14:31.590 --> 00:14:32.910 align:middle line:90%
Who does she think she is?

00:14:32.910 --> 00:14:33.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:14:33.170 --> 00:14:33.900 align:middle line:90%
>> You're way better.

00:14:33.900 --> 00:14:34.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:14:34.730 --> 00:14:35.926 align:middle line:90%
>> So am I.

00:14:35.926 --> 00:14:38.370 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:38.370 --> 00:14:42.060 align:middle line:84%
What I just did was to establish
rapport and closeness here

00:14:42.060 --> 00:14:44.652 align:middle line:90%
through exclusion.

00:14:44.652 --> 00:14:46.860 align:middle line:84%
So what you're doing-- and
this is the first movement

00:14:46.860 --> 00:14:47.660 align:middle line:90%
of shame--

00:14:47.660 --> 00:14:50.070 align:middle line:90%
is to triangulate internally.

00:14:50.070 --> 00:14:54.570 align:middle line:84%
The way to re-establish the
relationship with the parent

00:14:54.570 --> 00:14:57.720 align:middle line:84%
is to push a part
of yourself away.

00:14:57.720 --> 00:15:01.320 align:middle line:84%
So let's say that this is
the needy aspect, right?

00:15:01.320 --> 00:15:04.320 align:middle line:84%
So stand in front
of one another.

00:15:04.320 --> 00:15:08.190 align:middle line:90%
Right now, the psyche is united.

00:15:08.190 --> 00:15:10.720 align:middle line:84%
When we're first born,
there are some caveats,

00:15:10.720 --> 00:15:12.450 align:middle line:84%
but for the sake of
your understanding,

00:15:12.450 --> 00:15:13.950 align:middle line:84%
pretend that when
you're first born,

00:15:13.950 --> 00:15:18.030 align:middle line:84%
your psychology, your
being, is united.

00:15:18.030 --> 00:15:20.370 align:middle line:84%
And when we encounter
circumstances like this,

00:15:20.370 --> 00:15:22.260 align:middle line:90%
it can't stay united.

00:15:22.260 --> 00:15:26.580 align:middle line:84%
It actually has to fracture
and fragment in order to cope.

00:15:26.580 --> 00:15:28.020 align:middle line:84%
And so much of
what you're dealing

00:15:28.020 --> 00:15:30.510 align:middle line:84%
with in your adult life
that is causing you

00:15:30.510 --> 00:15:34.330 align:middle line:84%
problems is because of
this fragmentation process.

00:15:34.330 --> 00:15:37.020 align:middle line:84%
So in the moment that the mom
pushed her away like that,

00:15:37.020 --> 00:15:40.560 align:middle line:84%
she has to triangulate by
establishing closeness here,

00:15:40.560 --> 00:15:44.460 align:middle line:84%
by pushing the part of
her that needs away.

00:15:44.460 --> 00:15:47.090 align:middle line:84%
So show what that
looks like, physically.

00:15:47.090 --> 00:15:47.890 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:15:47.890 --> 00:15:50.520 align:middle line:90%


00:15:50.520 --> 00:15:53.470 align:middle line:90%
Look at the triangle.

00:15:53.470 --> 00:15:57.810 align:middle line:84%
Now this is all happening in
an invisible way, internally.

00:15:57.810 --> 00:16:01.230 align:middle line:84%
But what's set up here
now is a triangle,

00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:04.750 align:middle line:84%
whereby this one gets closer to
mom by pushing a part of itself

00:16:04.750 --> 00:16:05.550 align:middle line:90%
away.

00:16:05.550 --> 00:16:06.485 align:middle line:90%
This is what shame is.

00:16:06.485 --> 00:16:07.860 align:middle line:84%
This is your
definition of shame.

00:16:07.860 --> 00:16:08.660 align:middle line:90%
Ready?

00:16:08.660 --> 00:16:10.920 align:middle line:84%
I'm changing your
definition of shame.

00:16:10.920 --> 00:16:16.530 align:middle line:84%
Shame is to push
yourself away from you.

00:16:16.530 --> 00:16:17.970 align:middle line:90%
You can't do that, can you?

00:16:17.970 --> 00:16:20.130 align:middle line:90%
On a physical level.

00:16:20.130 --> 00:16:22.320 align:middle line:84%
Because obviously, if
I was to take a knife,

00:16:22.320 --> 00:16:23.990 align:middle line:84%
draw it down my body,
I can't do that.

00:16:23.990 --> 00:16:25.020 align:middle line:90%
I'm not living anymore.

00:16:25.020 --> 00:16:26.410 align:middle line:84%
That's not how
physicality works,

00:16:26.410 --> 00:16:29.130 align:middle line:84%
but it is how
consciousness works.

00:16:29.130 --> 00:16:31.110 align:middle line:84%
The way that I
manage to push myself

00:16:31.110 --> 00:16:35.500 align:middle line:84%
away is by splitting
myself in half.

00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:38.830 align:middle line:84%
Now the scary part-- and this
is where most of you are going

00:16:38.830 --> 00:16:43.160 align:middle line:84%
to relate to this
as a self-concept--

00:16:43.160 --> 00:16:45.230 align:middle line:90%
all of us have done this, OK?

00:16:45.230 --> 00:16:46.880 align:middle line:84%
So all of us have
parts of ourselves

00:16:46.880 --> 00:16:49.550 align:middle line:84%
that we experience
that rejection of,

00:16:49.550 --> 00:16:52.070 align:middle line:90%
and so we created that shame.

00:16:52.070 --> 00:16:55.520 align:middle line:84%
This is the biological
affective reaction

00:16:55.520 --> 00:16:57.260 align:middle line:84%
of pushing that part
away from ourselves.

00:16:57.260 --> 00:16:59.720 align:middle line:90%
All of us have done this.

00:16:59.720 --> 00:17:01.340 align:middle line:84%
But if you grew up
in a circumstance

00:17:01.340 --> 00:17:03.980 align:middle line:84%
where you were in specific
roles in childhood,

00:17:03.980 --> 00:17:06.140 align:middle line:90%
like the scapegoat--

00:17:06.140 --> 00:17:09.319 align:middle line:90%
you guys know what that is?

00:17:09.319 --> 00:17:11.540 align:middle line:84%
Well, in a dysfunctional
family home,

00:17:11.540 --> 00:17:15.089 align:middle line:84%
everybody has these
different roles.

00:17:15.089 --> 00:17:20.160 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, I
think I've probably

00:17:20.160 --> 00:17:23.819 align:middle line:84%
met two families in my lifetime
that don't fall somewhere

00:17:23.819 --> 00:17:26.619 align:middle line:90%
on the spectrum of dysfunction.

00:17:26.619 --> 00:17:29.187 align:middle line:84%
This is the way that a human
social group functions.

00:17:29.187 --> 00:17:30.270 align:middle line:90%
It goes beyond the family.

00:17:30.270 --> 00:17:32.790 align:middle line:84%
You see these
roles in companies.

00:17:32.790 --> 00:17:34.890 align:middle line:90%
You see them in sports teams.

00:17:34.890 --> 00:17:38.460 align:middle line:90%
Anywhere that humans congregate.

00:17:38.460 --> 00:17:42.040 align:middle line:84%
It's this funny way of trying
to establish relationships.

00:17:42.040 --> 00:17:44.370 align:middle line:84%
And the scapegoat
child in the family

00:17:44.370 --> 00:17:48.030 align:middle line:84%
is the carrier of
the family problem.

00:17:48.030 --> 00:17:49.920 align:middle line:84%
So what the family
first does is say, well,

00:17:49.920 --> 00:17:53.010 align:middle line:84%
that one's the one
with all the problems,

00:17:53.010 --> 00:17:55.290 align:middle line:84%
and now we're going to
get all of our self-esteem

00:17:55.290 --> 00:17:57.067 align:middle line:84%
by dealing with
that one's problems.

00:17:57.067 --> 00:17:58.650 align:middle line:84%
And it becomes the
way that the family

00:17:58.650 --> 00:18:00.400 align:middle line:90%
doesn't focus on themselves.

00:18:00.400 --> 00:18:02.385 align:middle line:84%
And the scapegoat
child is the nightmare

00:18:02.385 --> 00:18:04.260 align:middle line:84%
for people who are in
the psychological field

00:18:04.260 --> 00:18:06.720 align:middle line:84%
because mom and dad are
always dragging that kid in,

00:18:06.720 --> 00:18:08.880 align:middle line:90%
like, fix the kid.

00:18:08.880 --> 00:18:12.290 align:middle line:90%
And it's really not the kid.

00:18:12.290 --> 00:18:15.280 align:middle line:84%
So if you're in that type
of a dynamic in childhood,

00:18:15.280 --> 00:18:18.247 align:middle line:84%
you can imagine that this
happens over and over again.

00:18:18.247 --> 00:18:19.330 align:middle line:90%
I am a little bit curious.

00:18:19.330 --> 00:18:21.700 align:middle line:84%
How many of you would
relate to the idea

00:18:21.700 --> 00:18:25.840 align:middle line:84%
of having at least one parent
who you could not please?

00:18:25.840 --> 00:18:28.800 align:middle line:90%
So a fair bit.

00:18:28.800 --> 00:18:30.270 align:middle line:90%
Your self-concept of shame.

00:18:30.270 --> 00:18:33.930 align:middle line:90%


00:18:33.930 --> 00:18:37.200 align:middle line:84%
The reason is is because
you kept doing this, over

00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:38.110 align:middle line:90%
and over again.

00:18:38.110 --> 00:18:41.200 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't just the part of
you that's needy, right?

00:18:41.200 --> 00:18:44.130 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's the part of you
that poses as a competition

00:18:44.130 --> 00:18:45.630 align:middle line:90%
to that parent.

00:18:45.630 --> 00:18:48.720 align:middle line:84%
You ended up fracturing
like this over, and over,

00:18:48.720 --> 00:18:51.300 align:middle line:84%
and over, and over, in trying
to establish connection

00:18:51.300 --> 00:18:53.803 align:middle line:84%
with this parent by pushing
this part, and that part,

00:18:53.803 --> 00:18:56.220 align:middle line:84%
and this part, and that part,
and this part, and that part

00:18:56.220 --> 00:18:58.140 align:middle line:90%
away.

00:18:58.140 --> 00:19:04.910 align:middle line:84%
So now your self-concept is I'm
worth nothing, and I'm no good.

00:19:04.910 --> 00:19:08.000 align:middle line:84%
So if you've got that type
of a core self-concept,

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:11.223 align:middle line:84%
this triangulation has
happened over and over again.

00:19:11.223 --> 00:19:13.265 align:middle line:84%
You actually look internally
a bit like a matrix.

00:19:13.265 --> 00:19:17.100 align:middle line:90%


00:19:17.100 --> 00:19:19.775 align:middle line:84%
So do you want to know
how to remedy this issue?

00:19:19.775 --> 00:19:20.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:19:20.990 --> 00:19:23.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Now that I've made you
do a deep dive into hell?

00:19:23.640 --> 00:19:24.440 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:19:24.440 --> 00:19:28.030 align:middle line:90%


00:19:28.030 --> 00:19:31.860 align:middle line:84%
First, I'm actually
curious, what

00:19:31.860 --> 00:19:34.170 align:middle line:84%
are some of the strategies
that you have heard

00:19:34.170 --> 00:19:36.420 align:middle line:84%
other teachers talk
to you about in terms

00:19:36.420 --> 00:19:38.994 align:middle line:90%
of resolving your shame?

00:19:38.994 --> 00:19:40.398 align:middle line:90%
>> Self-love.

00:19:40.398 --> 00:19:41.810 align:middle line:90%
>> Embrace it.

00:19:41.810 --> 00:19:44.302 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that would be genius,
