00:19:48.440 --> 00:19:50.840 align:middle line:90%
>> Personal pet peeve.

00:19:50.840 --> 00:19:52.340 align:middle line:84%
I actually wrote a
book on self-love

00:19:52.340 --> 00:19:53.757 align:middle line:84%
because this was
driving me crazy,

00:19:53.757 --> 00:19:57.852 align:middle line:90%
because this is me as well.

00:19:57.852 --> 00:19:59.810 align:middle line:84%
When I was starting to
learn this whole process

00:19:59.810 --> 00:20:02.420 align:middle line:84%
of self-love, it drove me crazy
how many people would tell me,

00:20:02.420 --> 00:20:04.840 align:middle line:90%
you just need to love yourself.

00:20:04.840 --> 00:20:07.100 align:middle line:84%
But when this is your
life, it's like, well, you

00:20:07.100 --> 00:20:10.400 align:middle line:84%
might as well tell me to build
a rocket ship, to successfully

00:20:10.400 --> 00:20:13.130 align:middle line:84%
build a new colony on Mars,
because that would be easier.

00:20:13.130 --> 00:20:15.440 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:20:15.440 --> 00:20:18.680 align:middle line:84%
So I didn't understand
exactly what self-love meant.

00:20:18.680 --> 00:20:19.790 align:middle line:90%
I can show you up here.

00:20:19.790 --> 00:20:21.350 align:middle line:90%
I'm about to.

00:20:21.350 --> 00:20:23.450 align:middle line:84%
But the majority
of the strategies

00:20:23.450 --> 00:20:25.730 align:middle line:84%
that people have
for resolving shame

00:20:25.730 --> 00:20:28.670 align:middle line:84%
is to try to get you
to see that you're not

00:20:28.670 --> 00:20:31.730 align:middle line:84%
that negative thing that
you have disowned, rejected,

00:20:31.730 --> 00:20:32.850 align:middle line:90%
and denied.

00:20:32.850 --> 00:20:33.650 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:35.317 align:middle line:84%
So let's say that
you've got a woman who

00:20:35.317 --> 00:20:38.040 align:middle line:90%
feels like she's super fat.

00:20:38.040 --> 00:20:41.440 align:middle line:84%
Now most people who are dealing
with that fat-based shame

00:20:41.440 --> 00:20:44.230 align:middle line:84%
would say, well, let's look at
all the ways you're not fat.

00:20:44.230 --> 00:20:46.900 align:middle line:84%
Let's look at how
you're beautiful, right?

00:20:46.900 --> 00:20:48.790 align:middle line:84%
Actually, you've
enhanced the split.

00:20:48.790 --> 00:20:52.250 align:middle line:90%


00:20:52.250 --> 00:20:54.240 align:middle line:90%
Do you see why?

00:20:54.240 --> 00:20:57.970 align:middle line:84%
You're making the shame
worse with that strategy,

00:20:57.970 --> 00:21:00.780 align:middle line:90%
which is why it doesn't work.

00:21:00.780 --> 00:21:02.653 align:middle line:84%
Or why you go to
a seminar, and you

00:21:02.653 --> 00:21:05.070 align:middle line:84%
get a tiny bit of Novocaine,
and then it's done the second

00:21:05.070 --> 00:21:05.870 align:middle line:90%
you leave the room.

00:21:05.870 --> 00:21:09.000 align:middle line:90%
And you're back to square one.

00:21:09.000 --> 00:21:11.340 align:middle line:10%
But just to see if you can
mentally figure this out

00:21:11.340 --> 00:21:14.700 align:middle line:10%
for yourselves, looking
at this dynamic,

00:21:14.700 --> 00:21:17.310 align:middle line:10%
just physically, how
it's playing out here,

00:21:17.310 --> 00:21:20.880 align:middle line:10%
what is the solution to
shame, knowing that to shame

00:21:20.880 --> 00:21:23.100 align:middle line:10%
is to push something
away from yourself?

00:21:23.100 --> 00:21:24.138 align:middle line:10%
What's the remedy?

00:21:24.138 --> 00:21:25.890 align:middle line:10%
>> Pull it closer.

00:21:25.890 --> 00:21:27.790 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes.

00:21:27.790 --> 00:21:28.590 align:middle line:90%
So how?

00:21:28.590 --> 00:21:31.482 align:middle line:90%


00:21:31.482 --> 00:21:32.928 align:middle line:10%
>> [INAUDIBLE].

00:21:32.928 --> 00:21:37.266 align:middle line:90%


00:21:37.266 --> 00:21:41.567 align:middle line:10%
>> Naming it, like you
did, and then [INAUDIBLE]..

00:21:41.567 --> 00:21:42.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, naming it's good.

00:21:42.650 --> 00:21:43.460 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:21:43.460 --> 00:21:44.960 align:middle line:84%
It's good for us
to become conscious

00:21:44.960 --> 00:21:47.085 align:middle line:84%
of the parts of ourselves
that we are pushing away.

00:21:47.085 --> 00:21:50.480 align:middle line:90%


00:21:50.480 --> 00:21:52.850 align:middle line:90%
Compassion's the answer.

00:21:52.850 --> 00:21:54.380 align:middle line:84%
Compassion is the
antidote to shame.

00:21:54.380 --> 00:21:55.880 align:middle line:84%
Any of you who
brought your notebook

00:21:55.880 --> 00:21:57.213 align:middle line:90%
should be writing that one down.

00:21:57.213 --> 00:22:00.650 align:middle line:90%


00:22:00.650 --> 00:22:04.820 align:middle line:84%
Compassion is going to be
your first step towards love.

00:22:04.820 --> 00:22:09.023 align:middle line:84%
To love something is to take
something as part of yourself.

00:22:09.023 --> 00:22:10.940 align:middle line:84%
I want that to be your
new definition of love.

00:22:10.940 --> 00:22:12.590 align:middle line:84%
Because when people
are approaching

00:22:12.590 --> 00:22:16.730 align:middle line:84%
love as if it's this just
elated, emotional state,

00:22:16.730 --> 00:22:19.130 align:middle line:90%
you can't get there.

00:22:19.130 --> 00:22:20.925 align:middle line:84%
It's actually not
going to work for you.

00:22:20.925 --> 00:22:22.550 align:middle line:84%
If you have a part
of yourself that you

00:22:22.550 --> 00:22:25.970 align:middle line:84%
have been taught is
detestable, a part of you

00:22:25.970 --> 00:22:28.100 align:middle line:84%
that you've been
pushing away forever,

00:22:28.100 --> 00:22:30.410 align:middle line:84%
to try to just feel really
super warm and fuzzy

00:22:30.410 --> 00:22:33.630 align:middle line:84%
towards that aspect
isn't going to happen.

00:22:33.630 --> 00:22:36.560 align:middle line:90%
What can happen is curiosity.

00:22:36.560 --> 00:22:38.960 align:middle line:84%
Now compassion, this is
why I'm saying compassion

00:22:38.960 --> 00:22:42.650 align:middle line:84%
is actually the antidote
to the shame-based process,

00:22:42.650 --> 00:22:48.500 align:middle line:84%
because compassion arises from
commonality, from shared pain.

00:22:48.500 --> 00:22:53.620 align:middle line:84%
That means that the root of
compassion is understanding.

00:22:53.620 --> 00:22:55.310 align:middle line:84%
By raise of hands,
how many of you

00:22:55.310 --> 00:22:57.940 align:middle line:84%
have watched a movie
where there's a bad guy,

00:22:57.940 --> 00:22:59.690 align:middle line:84%
and everyone else in
that theater is like,

00:22:59.690 --> 00:23:01.460 align:middle line:90%
I hate that guy.

00:23:01.460 --> 00:23:03.915 align:middle line:84%
And you're like, oh,
crap, I relate to them.

00:23:03.915 --> 00:23:04.885 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:04.885 --> 00:23:07.310 align:middle line:90%


00:23:07.310 --> 00:23:09.170 align:middle line:84%
The reason you feel
that way, and you're not

00:23:09.170 --> 00:23:13.750 align:middle line:84%
pushing that part away, is
because you relate to them.

00:23:13.750 --> 00:23:16.450 align:middle line:90%
This is how to find compassion.

00:23:16.450 --> 00:23:17.830 align:middle line:84%
If you can't relate
to something,

00:23:17.830 --> 00:23:19.510 align:middle line:84%
you can't have
compassion for it.

00:23:19.510 --> 00:23:21.700 align:middle line:84%
And if you want to develop
compassion for something,

00:23:21.700 --> 00:23:24.350 align:middle line:90%
find out how to relate to it.

00:23:24.350 --> 00:23:27.560 align:middle line:84%
So if that means that you,
your central consciousness,

00:23:27.560 --> 00:23:30.580 align:middle line:84%
let's call it, you've
got to look at the aspect

00:23:30.580 --> 00:23:32.710 align:middle line:84%
that you really have
been pushing away,

00:23:32.710 --> 00:23:35.230 align:middle line:84%
the one that you currently
hate or have decided

00:23:35.230 --> 00:23:37.600 align:middle line:90%
is not appropriate.

00:23:37.600 --> 00:23:40.240 align:middle line:90%
And you try to relate to it.

00:23:40.240 --> 00:23:43.540 align:middle line:84%
That means I've got to develop
intimacy with that part.

00:23:43.540 --> 00:23:45.370 align:middle line:84%
Intimacy, by the
way, is the opposite

00:23:45.370 --> 00:23:47.230 align:middle line:90%
of pushing something away.

00:23:47.230 --> 00:23:52.600 align:middle line:84%
To have intimacy with something
is to feel into it, to see it

00:23:52.600 --> 00:23:56.170 align:middle line:84%
completely, to listen
to it, is to come

00:23:56.170 --> 00:23:58.870 align:middle line:84%
to a perfect understanding
of that thing.

00:23:58.870 --> 00:24:02.080 align:middle line:84%
So you've got to
dive deep into it.

